{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 09:29:07.371596", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"host_1_1_1_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_incorrect_netmask\"]\n\nRecommended immediate fix (not required for submission but actionable):\n- On host_1_1_1_1 reconfigure the interface to the correct netmask for the access subnet (likely 255.255.255.0, i.e., /24). Example (Linux):\n  - sudo ip addr flush dev eth0\n  - sudo ip addr add 10.1.1.2/24 dev eth0\n  - sudo ip route add default via 10.1.1.1\n- Verify:\n  - ip addr show dev eth0 (should show /24)\n  - ip neigh (should show ARP for gateway)\n  - ping 10.1.1.1 (gateway) then ping 10.200.0.2 (DNS)\n\nIf you want, I can also:\n- provide the exact command outputs used as evidence, or\n- run the same checks on other hosts in the same access segment to confirm isolation.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2180, "output_tokens": 241, "total_tokens": 2421, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
